==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pika
<hw>Pi"ka</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any
one of several species of tailless rodents of the genus
<gen>Ochotona</gen> (formerly <gen>Lagomys</gen>), resembling small
rabbits, but with short ears alnd legs. They inhabit the high mountains
of Asia and America. Called also <altname>calling hare</altname>, and
<altname>crying hare</altname> and <altname>rock rabbit</altname>. See
<er>Chief hare</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pike</ent>⟦br⟧
